  "description": "Finding 4 from technical debt analysis (B-14862851). In scheduler/followups.py, _create_followups() calls self.storage.list_beads() multiple times inside loops (lines 477, 492, 501), which is an O(n) call per iteration \u2014 this compounds as bead count grows. Fix: call list_beads() once at the start of _create_followups() and reuse the cached result throughout. Do not refactor the three near-identical creation blocks \u2014 that is a separate concern outside the scope of this bead.",
